@startuml llm-cli-proxy-architecture
!include _standard-style.puml

title LLM Subscription Provider Architecture (@rapid/llm-proxy)\nDirect HTTP + Claude Direct-OAuth with CLI Fallback (worker pool)\nv7.3 (2026-06-21)

top to bottom direction

package "Docker Container (coding-services)" {
  component [Semantic Analysis\nMCP Server] as semantic <<core>>
  component [LLM Service\n(Provider Registry)] as llmservice <<core>>
  component [Copilot Provider\n(proxy mode)] as copilotprov <<agent>>
  component [Claude Code Provider\n(proxy mode)] as claudeprov <<agent>>
  component [Anthropic Provider\n(api-key)] as anthropicprov <<api>>

  semantic -down-> llmservice : LLM requests
  llmservice -down-> copilotprov
  llmservice -down-> claudeprov
  llmservice -down-> anthropicprov
}

rectangle "host.docker.internal:12435" as hostbox {
  package "LLM Proxy Bridge (proxy-bridge/server.mjs)" {
    component [POST /api/complete\n(dispatcher)] as complete <<api>>
    component [GET /health] as health <<api>>
    component [/api/llm/settings\n(processOverrides)] as settings <<api>>
  }

  package "claude-code dispatcher" as claudebox {
    component [completeClaudeCodeDirect\n(direct OAuth bearer)] as cccdirect <<core>>
    component [completeClaudeCodeViaCLI\n(CLI subprocess, fallback)] as cccfall <<cli>>
    note right of cccdirect
      Path 1 — fast path
      ~0.9s end-to-end
      Real input/output tokens
      Used for ALL claude-code calls first
    end note
    note right of cccfall
      Path 2 — fallback only
      ~10-14s end-to-end
      Auto-injects ~16-22K system prompt
      (billed as cache_creation; cache_read
      on subsequent calls within 5 min)
      Different Anthropic rate-limit bucket
      than the bare OAuth bearer endpoint
    end note
  }

  component [Direct HTTP POST\nto Copilot API] as copilothttp <<api>>
}

cloud "External APIs" as cloud {
  component [api.anthropic.com\n/v1/messages] as anthropicapi <<external>>
  component [Copilot API\ncopilot-api.{enterprise}\n/ api.githubcopilot.com] as copilotapi <<external>>
}

database "Host Auth Stores" as auth {
  component [~/.local/share/opencode/auth.json\nCopilot OAuth token] as copilotauth <<storage>>
  component [macOS Keychain\nClaude Max OAuth\n(60s cache, expiry buffer)] as keychain <<storage>>
}

' Cross-boundary connections
copilotprov SYNC_LINE complete : HTTP via\nhost.docker.internal:12435
claudeprov SYNC_LINE complete : HTTP via\nhost.docker.internal:12435

' Dispatcher routing
complete -down-> copilothttp : copilot requests
complete -down-> claudebox : claude-code requests

' Direct OAuth → CLI fallback ladder (within claude-code dispatcher)
cccdirect -down-> cccfall : 401 / 403 / 429\n(shouldFallbackToCLI)

' External call paths
cccdirect SYNC_LINE anthropicapi : HTTPS POST\nAuthorization: Bearer <oauth>\nanthropic-version: 2023-06-01
cccfall SYNC_LINE anthropicapi : via `claude -p` subprocess\n(persistent stream-JSON worker pool — v7.3;\nsee claude-worker-pool-architecture)
copilothttp SYNC_LINE copilotapi : HTTPS POST\n/chat/completions

' Auth flow
cccdirect <.. keychain : reads access_token\n(re-reads when expiresAt - now < 60s\nOR on 401 from API)
cccfall <.. keychain : reads via CLI\n(CLI auto-refreshes on every call)
copilothttp <.. copilotauth : reads OAuth token\n(refresh every 60s)

note right of complete
  **Dispatcher behaviour (v7.1)**
  - Pinned provider goes first (Settings → processOverrides)
  - claude-code: direct → CLI fallback on auth/rate-limit
  - Same Max subscription on BOTH paths; only the
    rate-limit bucket differs
  - No cross-provider fallback for pinned providers —
    pinning expresses user intent, not "anything that works"
end note

note bottom of claudebox
  **Why fallback within claude-code instead of claude-code → copilot?**
  Anthropic 429s the OAuth bearer endpoint per-model. Haiku is fine;
  sonnet/opus get rate-limited on the bearer path. The CLI session
  endpoint uses a different bucket and the same Max subscription, so
  the call succeeds — just slower. v7.3 lands a persistent worker pool
  (Phases 62-63) that keeps the `claude -p` subprocess warm, bringing
  the CLI-fallback path from ~14s to ~2-3s. See
  claude-worker-pool-architecture + claude-worker-pool-lifecycle.
end note

note bottom of llmservice
  **Auto-route preference**
  Claude sessions → claude-code first, then copilot
  OpenCode/corporate → copilot first, then groq → openai → anthropic
  Per-process pinning overrides via /api/llm/settings
end note

@enduml
